{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Great is Yahweh, and greatly to be praised, in the city of our God, in his holy mountain."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Beautiful in elevation, the joy of the whole earth, is Mount Zion, on the north sides,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "the city of the great King."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "God has shown himself in her citadels as a refuge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For, behold, the kings assembled themselves, they passed by together."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They saw it, then they were amazed. They were dismayed."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They hurried away."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Trembling took hold of them there, pain, as of a woman in travail."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "With the east wind, you break the ships of Tarshish."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "As we have heard, so we have seen, in the city of Yahweh of Armies, in the city of our God. God will establish it forever. Selah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "We have thought about your loving kindness, God, in the middle of your temple."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "As is your name, God, so is your praise to the ends of the earth."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your right hand is full of righteousness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let Mount Zion be glad! Let the daughters of Judah rejoice because of your judgments."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Walk about Zion, and go around her. Number its towers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Notice her bulwarks. Consider her palaces,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "that you may tell it to the next generation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For this God is our God forever and ever. He will be our guide even to death."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}